00:31.800 --> 00:35.600
[Western-style music plays]

00:48.280 --> 00:50.521
[ Music continues ]

00:50.560 --> 00:52.528
[ Bird screeches]

01:06.480 --> 01:09.484
[ Music continues ]

01:17.280 --> 01:19.408
BRIAN: [ Coughing ]

01:22.080 --> 01:24.242
Oh. [ Grunts ]

01:28.720 --> 01:30.722
[ Groans ]

01:38.040 --> 01:40.691
[Coughing ]

01:45.440 --> 01:47.568
[Coughing ]

01:53.920 --> 01:55.843
[Breathing heavily]

02:05.840 --> 02:08.047
[ Music continues ]

02:42.720 --> 02:45.564
[Siren wailing ]

03:34.200 --> 03:37.329
[Wailing continues]

03:54.640 --> 03:57.041
[ Engine shuts off]

03:57.080 --> 03:59.924
[Suspenseful music plays]

04:17.200 --> 04:19.601
OLSON: [Spits ]

04:24.280 --> 04:25.725
SAMUEL: Fuck me.

04:25.760 --> 04:28.491
OLSON: Paperwork on this one's

04:28.520 --> 04:32.445
giving me
a pain in the ass already.

04:32.480 --> 04:34.448
SAMUEL: Jesus.

04:34.480 --> 04:38.326
What the hell happened?

04:38.360 --> 04:40.249
OLSON:
Well, one thing's for sure...

04:40.280 --> 04:44.205
The Grim Reaper
had himself a good old time.

04:45.840 --> 04:47.763
Samuel...

04:47.800 --> 04:49.609
you better call this in
to the city.

04:49.640 --> 04:52.803
They're gonna want to send out
some CSI technicians.

04:52.840 --> 04:54.888
Don't want us small-town boys

04:54.920 --> 04:56.763
contaminatin' evidence,
do they?

04:56.800 --> 04:58.928
SAMUEL: Yes, sir.

05:02.720 --> 05:04.006
OLSON: Samuel!

05:04.040 --> 05:05.883
Hold on there.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.287
Jackpot. Oh, my God.

05:13.320 --> 05:15.721
SAMUEL: Looks like somebody
tried to rip somebody off

05:15.760 --> 05:17.250
and got killed.

05:17.280 --> 05:18.520
OLSON: It sure looks like it.

05:18.560 --> 05:20.483
Where you goin' now?

05:20.520 --> 05:22.841
SAMUEL: I'm going to call it in.
Why?

05:22.880 --> 05:24.211
OLSON: I said, "Hold on here."

05:24.240 --> 05:25.844
SAMUEL:
With all this blow and cash,

05:25.880 --> 05:28.360
we're just askin' for trouble
just being around it.

05:28.400 --> 05:30.209
OLSON: Not if no one knows it.

05:30.240 --> 05:32.129
SAMUEL: You're kidding, right?

05:32.160 --> 05:34.606
OLSON: [Chuckles]
Just think about it, Samuel.

05:34.640 --> 05:39.601
That must be $3 million in cash
in that van.

05:39.640 --> 05:42.883
At least that much in product
in the other one.

05:42.920 --> 05:44.809
No one knows it's out here.

05:44.840 --> 05:47.605
SAMUEL: Bullshit.
Somebody always knows.

05:47.640 --> 05:50.803
OLSON: Didn't your wife
just have a baby?

05:50.840 --> 05:52.490
SAMUEL: Yes, sir.

05:52.520 --> 05:55.444
OLSON: I got two...
on the way to college.

05:55.480 --> 05:58.370
I don't know how the hell
I'm gonna pay their tuition.

05:58.400 --> 06:02.246
Room and board.
That's a lot of money, son.

06:02.280 --> 06:04.886
And I'll be honest...

06:04.920 --> 06:08.208
I'm feelin' old. I'm tired.

06:08.240 --> 06:10.720
Tired of workin' two jobs.

06:10.760 --> 06:13.889
Tired of pickin' up drunks
at 2:00 in the mornin'

06:13.920 --> 06:15.524
covered in piss and vomit.

06:15.560 --> 06:18.564
Tired of gettin' shot at
by some crazy bitch

06:18.600 --> 06:20.728
'cause her alimony check
bounced.

06:20.760 --> 06:23.525
I'm just tired.

06:23.560 --> 06:28.327
And, son,
that's a lot of money.

06:31.160 --> 06:33.891
[ Chuckles, laughs ]

06:36.440 --> 06:38.124
Had you going, kid, didn't I?

06:38.160 --> 06:41.448
SAMUEL: You son of a bitch.

06:41.480 --> 06:43.767
You almost had me.

06:43.840 --> 06:47.128
I'm gonna go call it in.

06:47.160 --> 06:50.403
OLSON: Sorry, kid.

06:53.280 --> 06:56.204
[Western-style music plays]

07:45.600 --> 07:47.489
Just take it easy, now.

07:47.520 --> 07:49.329
Let's talk this through.

07:49.360 --> 07:51.124
BRIAN: Like you did
with that young deputy there?

07:51.160 --> 07:53.561
OLSON:
I'm not worried about him.

07:53.600 --> 07:55.728
I'm worried about you and me.

07:55.760 --> 07:57.649
BRIAN: Don't even try.

07:57.680 --> 08:00.160
OLSON:
Uh, who the hell are you?

08:03.640 --> 08:06.291
[ Body thuds ]

08:07.720 --> 08:09.643
BRIAN: I have no idea.

08:09.680 --> 08:12.411
[Western-style music plays]

08:21.560 --> 08:23.927
[ Engine turns over]

08:34.440 --> 08:36.841
[ Music continues ]

08:42.400 --> 08:44.641
Fuck.

08:54.440 --> 08:56.886
[ Monitor beeping ]

09:01.360 --> 09:02.441
BLACK: Excuse me, sir.
A moment?

09:02.520 --> 09:03.681
DOCTOR: Yeah.

09:03.720 --> 09:05.529
BLACK: Is that the sheriff?

09:05.560 --> 09:09.804
DOCTOR: He's lucky to be alive.
Being prepped for surgery.

09:12.120 --> 09:14.361
Anything else?

09:16.600 --> 09:19.444
<i>ROCKER: Agent Rocker, DEA.</i>

09:19.480 --> 09:23.371
[Western-style music plays]

09:23.400 --> 09:25.562
The second he wakes up.
I need to know.

09:25.600 --> 09:29.400
DOCTOR: You got it.

09:30.960 --> 09:32.689
<i>ROCKER:
Let's go piece this together -</i>

09:32.720 --> 09:34.927
before the local cops
mess it up.

09:34.960 --> 09:37.611
COLE: We estimate that
nearly 1,000 pounds of cocaine

09:37.680 --> 09:40.331
was brought in
right beneath our noses.

09:40.360 --> 09:41.930
We're on the front line.

09:41.960 --> 09:45.248
And on the front line,
we can't afford to fuck up.

09:45.280 --> 09:47.965
[Western-style music plays]

09:49.960 --> 09:51.564
Breaking up these drug cartels

09:51.600 --> 09:54.604
and stemming the flow
of drugs, weapons, and cash

09:54.640 --> 09:58.850
across the Southwest border
is our top and only priority.

09:58.880 --> 10:00.291
I'm all ears.

10:00.320 --> 10:02.163
TAYLOR: A shit storm
in the middle of nowhere

10:02.200 --> 10:03.406
and a dead deputy.

10:03.440 --> 10:05.442
COLE: Davis, I need you
on traffic cams.

10:05.480 --> 10:07.608
Report back to me A.S.A.P.
DAVIS: I'm on it.

10:07.640 --> 10:09.290
- COLE: A dead deputy?
- TAYLOR: Yeah.

10:09.320 --> 10:11.766
[Western-style music plays]

10:11.800 --> 10:13.404
[Bird cawing]

11:01.360 --> 11:03.966
ROOKER: Looks like
we're missing someone.

11:04.000 --> 11:06.651
TECHNICIAN:
There's a vehicle missing, also.

11:09.320 --> 11:11.607
ROOKER:
You know the make and model?

11:11.640 --> 11:13.608
TECHNICIAN: I believe so.

11:17.440 --> 11:19.602
ROOKER: I want roadblocks
on every highway,

11:19.640 --> 11:21.210
people in trains
and bus stations.

11:21.240 --> 11:24.323
And check the hospitals.
This man is wounded.

11:24.360 --> 11:25.930
BLACK: Copy that.

11:25.960 --> 11:28.440
ROOKER: Take me through it.

11:28.480 --> 11:31.370
TECHNICIAN: We haven't
processed everything yet.

11:31.400 --> 11:32.686
I don't have half the data.

11:32.720 --> 11:34.210
ROOKER:
Tell me what you do have.

11:34.240 --> 11:36.527
TECHNICIAN: Well, right now
it's all guesswork.

11:36.560 --> 11:38.289
ROOKER:
Just... take a stab at it.

11:38.320 --> 11:40.527
TECHNICIAN:
I think our missing friend here

11:40.560 --> 11:42.562
caused most of the damage.

11:42.600 --> 11:46.525
He came out with a two-piece.
Took out perp one and perp two.

11:46.600 --> 11:50.161
Perp three and five,
they got a lot of rounds off.

11:50.200 --> 11:51.725
A lot of shooting.

11:51.760 --> 11:54.491
Nothin' hit. I think they may
have hit one of their own.

11:54.520 --> 11:57.091
I'm still checking
the trajectory on that.

11:57.120 --> 11:59.726
I mean, this guy,
he probably dropped his piece

11:59.760 --> 12:02.240
when he was countin' rounds.

12:02.280 --> 12:03.770
- And that's...
- ROOKER: Smart.

12:03.800 --> 12:07.043
TECHNICIAN: Yeah.
Well, he did take one.

12:07.120 --> 12:08.929
When perp six
hit him in the chest,

12:08.960 --> 12:11.327
perp number seven
made contact down below.

12:11.360 --> 12:13.283
That would explain the blood.

12:13.320 --> 12:14.685
ROOKER:
What about the chest hit?

12:14.720 --> 12:16.006
TECHNICIAN: We found a vest.

12:16.040 --> 12:18.486
Had some damage
and some blood on it.

12:18.520 --> 12:21.171
ROOKER: [ Sighs ]

12:21.200 --> 12:23.123
So he was prepared.

12:23.160 --> 12:24.969
TECHNICIAN: Or lucky.

12:25.000 --> 12:28.288
ROOKER: Okay, so, he was down

12:28.320 --> 12:30.561
and there were
still three men standing?

12:30.600 --> 12:32.602
TECHNICIAN: Clearly he cracked
his head pretty good

12:32.640 --> 12:33.846
when he fell down.

12:33.880 --> 12:36.087
He was down, but not out.

12:36.120 --> 12:37.565
Not immediately.

12:39.160 --> 12:40.810
ROOKER: How long before we have

12:40.840 --> 12:43.923
a more complete
ballistics report?

12:43.960 --> 12:47.248
TECHNICIAN: 24 hours. Maybe 36.

12:47.280 --> 12:50.602
ROOKER: Mm-hmm.

12:50.640 --> 12:52.927
I can live with that.

12:53.000 --> 12:54.889
TECHNICIAN: As of yet,
we still haven't determined

12:54.960 --> 12:56.405
who our mystery guest is.

12:56.440 --> 13:00.889
We're hoping something comes up
on his DNA report.

13:00.920 --> 13:04.641
[ Music intensifies]

13:07.920 --> 13:10.127
ROOKER: Somebody knows.

13:21.000 --> 13:23.765
Somebody always knows.

13:29.800 --> 13:31.643
Ah, great.

13:35.440 --> 13:39.365
MIKE: Just here to lend you
some local support.

13:39.400 --> 13:43.246
ROOKER:
Just don't get in my way.

13:45.200 --> 13:48.044
MIKE:
Heard you were an asshole.

13:57.560 --> 14:00.211
[Western-style music plays]

14:14.560 --> 14:19.248
PEREZ: Find out
how and why this happened.

14:21.040 --> 14:24.965
And find out
where they're taking the bodies.

14:27.360 --> 14:30.728
And I don't care how you do it.

14:30.760 --> 14:33.525
Find a way to get me his body.

14:54.160 --> 14:55.730
[ Engine shuts off]

14:55.760 --> 14:58.127
[ Car door opens, closes ]

15:05.160 --> 15:08.960
BRIAN: [ Coughing ]

15:21.960 --> 15:23.325
[ Bell rings ]

15:23.400 --> 15:26.006
CLERK: Mm-hmm. Yes, baby.

15:26.040 --> 15:28.850
Oh, babe, you make me laugh.
I miss you so much.

15:28.880 --> 15:31.451
BRIAN: You got a bathroom?

15:31.480 --> 15:34.290
CLERK: Yeah.
It's right over there.

15:34.320 --> 15:36.607
BRIAN: Thanks.

15:36.640 --> 15:39.246
CLERK: All right.
I should probably go.

15:39.280 --> 15:40.611
Someone's in the store.

15:40.640 --> 15:43.405
BRIAN: [Breathing heavily]

15:47.080 --> 15:48.969
[ Faucet squeaks ]

15:49.000 --> 15:51.970
[Suspenseful music plays]

15:54.640 --> 15:57.086
[Breathing heavily]

15:57.120 --> 16:00.169
[Pills rattling]

16:03.880 --> 16:07.851
[ Music intensifies]

16:09.160 --> 16:11.766
[ Groans, breathes sharply]

16:16.840 --> 16:18.251
[Gasps, sighs]

16:26.040 --> 16:27.280
[Pills rattling]

16:33.480 --> 16:36.927
Phew.

16:52.120 --> 16:54.168
Brian Barnes?

16:54.240 --> 16:57.403
[ Engine turns over]

17:11.680 --> 17:14.286
CLERK: Thanks for calling
the Streamline Bus Station.

17:14.319 --> 17:17.483
Bus leaves at 11:00.
All right. Later!

17:17.520 --> 17:18.931
[ Door opens ]

17:20.599 --> 17:22.409
How can I help you?

17:22.440 --> 17:24.329
BRIAN: I need a locker, please.

17:26.240 --> 17:29.289
CLERK: 703.
It's in the next room.

17:40.520 --> 17:41.851
Have a good day.

17:41.880 --> 17:43.530
[ Door opens ]

17:43.560 --> 17:46.166
[ Engine shuts off]

17:46.200 --> 17:48.407
[Cellphone buzzing]

17:56.240 --> 17:58.561
[Cellphone beeping]

18:35.480 --> 18:37.130
OFFICER: Excuse me, sir.

18:37.160 --> 18:39.606
This is a fire lane.
You can't park here.

18:39.680 --> 18:42.684
BRIAN: I'm sorry, Officer. I was
just looking at some directions.

18:42.720 --> 18:44.688
OFFICER: Have a good day.

18:45.840 --> 18:47.569
[ Engine turns over]

18:58.720 --> 19:00.370
[ Up-tempo pop music playing]

19:20.720 --> 19:24.805
OLSON: Oh, shit.

19:28.120 --> 19:30.487
ROOKER: Morning, Sheriff.

19:32.000 --> 19:33.081
Well...

19:33.120 --> 19:36.886
[Sighs]
afternoon at this point.

19:39.400 --> 19:41.368
Please don't get up.

19:44.400 --> 19:47.244
No need to bring
anyone else in here.

19:47.280 --> 19:51.604
DEA, they wanted me to wait,
but...

19:53.560 --> 19:56.166
Well, you see, this situation
is a bit time-sensitive.

19:56.200 --> 19:58.931
So, what happened, Sheriff?

19:58.960 --> 20:00.928
OLSON: [Sighs ]

20:03.120 --> 20:08.081
Well, there's not much to say.

20:08.120 --> 20:10.407
We responded to a call.

20:12.480 --> 20:19.364
Couple of hunters saw somethin'
out at, uh, Morris property.

20:19.400 --> 20:21.687
We checked it out.

20:24.040 --> 20:25.690
You know the rest.

20:26.760 --> 20:28.888
ROOKER: See, I don't, really.

20:28.920 --> 20:34.245
Let's just say
you take me through it.

20:34.280 --> 20:36.203
All of it.

20:44.000 --> 20:45.764
CHRISTINE: [ Humming ]

20:48.600 --> 20:51.251
Shit. OW! Oh.

20:51.280 --> 20:53.806
[Western-style music plays]

20:57.280 --> 20:58.930
HOWARD: What's wrong, cupcake?

20:58.960 --> 21:01.566
[ Music continues ]

21:02.920 --> 21:04.160
What's wrong?

21:04.240 --> 21:05.890
Did you burn yourself?

21:05.920 --> 21:08.446
- HOWARD: Ah.
- CHRISTINE: Mm.

21:08.480 --> 21:10.608
- HOWARD: Mm.
- CHRISTINE: I'm fine.

21:10.640 --> 21:13.120
HOWARD: Look, it's not so bad.
Not so bad.

21:13.160 --> 21:14.969
CHRISTINE: That's because
it's not your hand.

21:15.000 --> 21:18.766
That's why it's not so bad.
[ Chuckles ]

21:20.720 --> 21:23.087
Not now, baby.

21:23.120 --> 21:26.090
- HOWARD: Hey, baby.
- CHRISTINE: [ Chuckles ]

21:26.120 --> 21:29.329
- HOWARD: Who's asking?
- CHRISTINE: Not now.

21:29.360 --> 21:31.886
[ Grunts ] - HOWARD: Hey.

21:31.920 --> 21:34.002
What I want...

21:34.040 --> 21:36.168
when I want...

21:36.200 --> 21:40.171
and absolutely where I want...

21:40.200 --> 21:43.807
[ Buckles thuds ]
...is all you need to know.

21:43.840 --> 21:45.604
It's time to come to Daddy.

21:45.640 --> 21:48.291
That's right.
Talk to me like that.

21:48.320 --> 21:51.961
You know what?
I just want this right.

21:52.000 --> 21:53.525
Know what?

21:53.560 --> 21:56.723
I want you to start talkin'
to me like I like it, okay?

21:56.760 --> 21:58.046
No. I don't think so.

21:58.080 --> 21:59.684
Put it down.

21:59.720 --> 22:02.166
Put it down. [ Buckle thuds ]

22:02.200 --> 22:03.326
Okay.

22:03.360 --> 22:08.241
Now nice and easy.

22:08.280 --> 22:09.850
Yeah, one more time.

22:09.880 --> 22:13.487
You're gonna give it to me
just like I like it.

22:13.560 --> 22:17.645
Now you just do
exactly what I say.

22:17.680 --> 22:19.091
Here we go.

22:29.800 --> 22:32.041
[Tires screech ]

22:38.480 --> 22:40.847
[Horn blares]

22:40.920 --> 22:42.763
[Sighs]

22:44.680 --> 22:47.490
What the fuck?!
CHRISTINE: [Sighs]

22:47.520 --> 22:50.000
HOWARD: You just stay here.

22:50.040 --> 22:53.249
[ Door opens ]

22:58.960 --> 23:01.770
Hey!

23:01.800 --> 23:03.564
Hey, buddy!
[ Pounding on window]

23:04.240 --> 23:05.730
Hey, buddy?

23:05.760 --> 23:07.046
Hey!

23:10.480 --> 23:12.403
Hey, buddy, are you okay?
[Horn honks]

23:12.440 --> 23:13.566
Hey! Hey-

23:13.600 --> 23:15.409
Hey. Easy, man.

23:15.440 --> 23:17.568
Easy. I just wanted
to make sure you're okay.

23:17.600 --> 23:19.284
- BRIAN: Back off.
- HOWARD: Just lower the gun.

23:19.320 --> 23:22.290
Let's talk about this.
Easy, easy, okay?!

23:22.320 --> 23:24.209
Just lower the gun, all right?

23:24.240 --> 23:26.402
Just, can we...
Can we talk about this?

23:26.440 --> 23:27.601
BRIAN: Where am I?

23:27.640 --> 23:28.880
- Huh?
- HOWARD: Sorry?

23:28.920 --> 23:30.285
BRIAN: Who the fuck are you?

23:30.320 --> 23:32.288
HOWARD: Look,
I-I fuckin' live here, man.

23:32.320 --> 23:33.731
Look, I'll drive you
any place you want to go.

23:33.760 --> 23:35.410
BRIAN: Get back in the house.

23:35.440 --> 23:37.169
- HOWARD: No, I'll drive you!
- BRIAN: Back in the house now!

23:37.200 --> 23:38.804
- HOWARD: All right, all right!
- BRIAN: You hear me? Move!

23:38.840 --> 23:40.285
HOWARD: Just don't harm us, man.
Shit!

23:40.320 --> 23:42.800
- BRIAN: Let's go.
- HOWARD: All right.

23:42.840 --> 23:44.171
BRIAN: Do as I say,
and no one gets hurt.

23:44.200 --> 23:46.441
- Hey!
- HOWARD: Okay. Okay.

23:46.480 --> 23:48.005
- BRIAN: Get down!
- HOWARD: All right!

23:48.040 --> 23:49.769
Listen, man. I-I can help you.
BRIAN: Shut up!

23:49.800 --> 23:51.768
CHRISTINE: Please don't do this.
You don't have to do this.

23:51.800 --> 23:52.847
BRIAN:
I need to think a second.

23:52.880 --> 23:54.041
I need to think. All right.

23:54.080 --> 23:55.570
I can't call the cops.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.284
HOWARD: Hey, look. We won't
call the cops. I promise.

23:57.320 --> 23:59.527
Just... tell me
what you need, man.

24:02.560 --> 24:04.244
- BRIAN: Okay. You got a garage?
- HOWARD: Yeah.

24:04.280 --> 24:05.691
- BRIAN: You got rope?
- HOWARD: Sure.

24:05.720 --> 24:06.846
- BRIAN: Get up. Get up.
- HOWARD: Yeah. Okay.

24:06.880 --> 24:08.166
BRIAN: Listen to me!

24:08.200 --> 24:09.611
From now on, we all move
as a unit, all right?

24:09.640 --> 24:11.404
You do what I say,
and you'll be fine.

24:11.440 --> 24:12.930
Move! Now.
HOWARD: Just don't hurt us.

24:12.960 --> 24:15.725
Just... Okay. Here we are.

24:20.520 --> 24:22.409
MAN: Fuck.

24:22.480 --> 24:24.926
Fuck.

24:24.960 --> 24:27.361
I knew I shouldn't have
came into work today.

24:29.040 --> 24:32.408
[Suspenseful music plays]

24:47.520 --> 24:50.046
[Chains dangling ]

25:21.840 --> 25:24.810
PEREZ: [ Breathes deeply]

25:26.640 --> 25:29.530
I promised your mother.

25:29.560 --> 25:31.961
I promised her.

25:32.000 --> 25:34.367
[Sighs]

25:34.400 --> 25:36.767
Now look what I let happen.

25:39.080 --> 25:43.005
I wouldn't let you work with me.

25:43.040 --> 25:45.247
So what do you do?

25:45.280 --> 25:47.931
Go join
the fucking police force...

25:47.960 --> 25:50.201
under a different name.

25:56.080 --> 25:58.686
[Voice breaking] It's my fault.

25:58.720 --> 26:02.202
I...
I should have kept you closer.

26:04.880 --> 26:07.690
I should have kept
an eye on you.

26:10.720 --> 26:13.007
[Sighs]

26:25.520 --> 26:27.488
It's my fault.

26:30.880 --> 26:33.360
It's my fault.

26:39.480 --> 26:41.005
Tell me you have a name.

26:41.040 --> 26:45.887
JOSEPH: We have someone who
might be able to give us one.

26:47.400 --> 26:50.529
PEREZ: Let's go have
a little chat with someone.

26:53.600 --> 26:56.001
I don't want him left alone.

26:56.040 --> 26:58.520
Someone stays with him
day and night.

27:03.360 --> 27:05.408
And he stays above ground

27:05.440 --> 27:10.765
until the son of a bitch
that did this no longer is.

27:15.000 --> 27:16.729
[Chains dangling ]

27:20.720 --> 27:22.722
[speaking Spanish]

27:22.760 --> 27:25.650
PRISONER: Ah. Please.

27:26.840 --> 27:28.205
PEREZ: Now I'm gonna show you

27:28.240 --> 27:31.767
what happens
when you steal money from me.

27:31.800 --> 27:33.404
PRISONER: I didn't
steal anything from you!

27:33.440 --> 27:36.250
I would never steal
anything from you. Please!

27:38.160 --> 27:41.004
BRIAN: I need y'all to be quiet.
You understand me?

27:42.800 --> 27:44.723
HOWARD: Fuck.

27:44.760 --> 27:46.285
[ Door slams ]

28:06.800 --> 28:10.043
[Suspenseful music plays]

28:13.760 --> 28:15.762
BRIAN: [ Breathes sharply]

28:15.800 --> 28:18.406
[Sighs]

28:18.440 --> 28:20.966
[ Refrigerator door opens ]

28:24.280 --> 28:26.521
[Breathing heavily]

28:26.560 --> 28:28.608
[Sighs]

28:35.880 --> 28:40.169
HOWARD: Today of all clays.

28:40.200 --> 28:43.249
I could be playin' golf
on the back nine.

28:43.280 --> 28:45.362
CHRISTINE: That's what
you're thinkin' about right now,

28:45.400 --> 28:46.606
is golf?

28:46.640 --> 28:47.971
HOWARD: But now I'm tied up
in my own garage.

28:48.000 --> 28:49.889
This is good.
Thank you. Thank you.

28:49.920 --> 28:51.365
You got any ideas?

28:51.400 --> 28:53.687
[ Computer beeps ]

29:03.640 --> 29:05.961
COLE: What are you up to?

29:08.720 --> 29:10.563
Black.

29:10.600 --> 29:13.968
I just got word from my contact
at the hospital security.

29:14.000 --> 29:16.651
The good sheriff
has checked himself out early.

29:16.680 --> 29:17.727
BLACK: Copy that.

29:17.760 --> 29:19.762
Okay.

29:19.800 --> 29:21.450
You are not gonna believe this.

29:21.480 --> 29:26.327
The good old sheriff discharged
himself against doctor's orders.

29:26.360 --> 29:27.805
ROOKER: Mm.

29:29.800 --> 29:33.168
Damn right it was
against doctor's orders.

29:36.120 --> 29:40.125
Now, why would a man,
a drugged-up man,

29:40.160 --> 29:42.731
get out of his hospital bed

29:42.800 --> 29:45.804
and walk around
with his ear blown off?

29:45.840 --> 29:47.444
BLACK: I have no idea.

29:47.480 --> 29:50.723
ROOKER: Because he's running
from something or to somewhere.

29:50.760 --> 29:51.841
OFFICER: Here.

29:51.880 --> 29:53.962
The only vehicle
in that time frame

29:54.000 --> 29:57.129
that has matching tire tracks.

29:57.160 --> 29:59.527
ROOKER:
Just find out where he's going.

30:02.840 --> 30:04.490
Stay on the sheriff.

30:04.520 --> 30:05.885
And be careful.

30:05.920 --> 30:08.844
I'm pretty sure
he's a complete piece of shit

30:08.880 --> 30:10.484
hiding behind a badge.

30:10.520 --> 30:12.010
BLACK: Copy that.

30:17.480 --> 30:20.609
ROOKER: Get me a clear view
of that license plate.

30:37.000 --> 30:40.482
[Pills rattling]

30:54.560 --> 30:57.803
[Suspenseful music plays]

31:19.960 --> 31:22.088
OLSON: Ahh.

31:22.120 --> 31:24.407
Oh.

31:24.440 --> 31:26.886
Baby, I missed you.

31:33.920 --> 31:35.763
Ahh.

31:51.000 --> 31:53.128
[Telephone rings]

31:58.280 --> 32:01.807
[ Ringing continues]

32:01.840 --> 32:05.640
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

32:05.680 --> 32:07.523
[Cellphone beeps]

32:07.560 --> 32:09.403
Hey, Mike.

32:09.440 --> 32:11.568
MIKE: I was looking for you
at the hospital.

32:11.600 --> 32:13.762
OLSON: Yeah, well,
I saw myself out.

32:13.800 --> 32:16.406
That's no place for me
to get better, is it?

32:16.440 --> 32:18.090
MIKE: I hear you.

32:18.120 --> 32:21.044
We've got a bit of a problem
down here, though.

32:21.080 --> 32:24.448
Seems somehow
we misplaced Sammy's body.

32:24.480 --> 32:26.562
OLSON: What the hell
are you talkin' about?

32:26.600 --> 32:29.524
How the hell
do you misplace a body?

32:29.560 --> 32:32.006
MIKE: No clue.

32:32.040 --> 32:33.804
OLSON: You're serious?

32:33.840 --> 32:36.969
Well, what... what
about the ballistics?

32:37.000 --> 32:41.005
MIKE: We never got a chance
to even process him.

32:45.720 --> 32:49.122
OLSON: Now, Mike,
that's just terrible.

32:49.160 --> 32:51.606
Any idea
where the body went now?

32:51.640 --> 32:53.802
MIKE: Fuck if anyone knows.

32:53.840 --> 32:56.764
It's gone poof. Vanished.

32:56.800 --> 32:58.689
OLSON: No shit.

33:00.720 --> 33:02.848
[Doorknob rattling]

33:05.080 --> 33:08.323
Mike, I'm gonna have
to call you back.

33:08.360 --> 33:11.204
I'll get...
I'll get right back to you.

33:17.920 --> 33:20.002
[ Keys jingling]

33:22.280 --> 33:24.521
[ Lock disengages ]

33:27.400 --> 33:28.765
JOSEPH: [ Gasps ]

33:37.000 --> 33:39.890
OLSON: Son of a bitch.
Break in my house?

33:39.920 --> 33:41.684
[Gun cocks]

33:41.720 --> 33:45.691
PEREZ: Hi, Sheriff.
We need to talk.

33:48.520 --> 33:51.251
Sit down!

33:51.280 --> 33:53.806
[speaking Spanish]

33:58.360 --> 34:03.161
You nervous, Sheriff?
You look nervous.

34:03.200 --> 34:06.249
OLSON: Yeah, well,
it's been a long day.

34:06.280 --> 34:10.170
PEREZ: You know,
I heard about that.

34:10.199 --> 34:12.965
But I got a problem
I think you can help me with.

34:13.000 --> 34:15.844
OLSON: Okay. What's that?

34:15.880 --> 34:19.168
PEREZ: Now, you know me.
You know who I am.

34:19.199 --> 34:21.440
OLSON:
Everybody knows who you are.

34:24.400 --> 34:28.291
PEREZ: Someone stole
a lot of money from me.

34:28.320 --> 34:30.766
That I can live with.

34:30.800 --> 34:36.409
But where you can help me is
to figure out who killed my men.

34:36.440 --> 34:39.364
OLSON: First of all,
I'm gonna tell you...

34:39.400 --> 34:42.449
When we got there,
they were already dead...

34:42.480 --> 34:48.487
except for the one...
who shot me in the goddamn ear.

34:50.639 --> 34:53.120
PEREZ:
You're alive, aren't you?

34:53.159 --> 34:55.731
OLSON: Uh-huh.
Look, I just don't know.

34:55.760 --> 34:59.242
I just don't know
how I can help you, Mateo.

34:59.280 --> 35:01.203
PEREZ: One of them was my son.

35:01.240 --> 35:02.890
OLSON:
I'm real sorry to hear that.

35:02.920 --> 35:08.086
But like I said, when I got
there, they were already dead.

35:08.120 --> 35:12.045
PEREZ: My son was with you.

35:19.160 --> 35:22.642
OLSON: I'm sorry. I...

35:22.680 --> 35:25.411
Sam was a good deputy.

35:25.440 --> 35:27.727
I-I didn't know.

35:34.280 --> 35:36.726
PEREZ:
About that guy that shot you...

35:36.760 --> 35:39.809
OLSON:
Look, he shot both of us.

35:39.840 --> 35:42.810
He shot Sammy,
and... and I tried to help him,

35:42.840 --> 35:43.762
and he shot me!

35:43.800 --> 35:46.167
Look, we thought they were dead.

35:46.200 --> 35:47.645
PEREZ: Tell me about him.

35:47.680 --> 35:51.366
OLSON:
I saw his face for 30 seconds.

35:51.400 --> 35:53.129
And then he shot me.

35:53.160 --> 35:54.491
I wish there was more,

35:54.520 --> 35:56.249
but I never saw
this guy before in my life.

35:56.280 --> 36:00.410
I swear to God. I have
no idea who these people are.

36:00.440 --> 36:03.364
PEREZ:
Maybe you can help me find him.

36:06.040 --> 36:08.930
Unless you were planning
on going somewhere.

36:08.960 --> 36:10.325
OLSON:
I don't know what I can do.

36:10.360 --> 36:12.931
The DEA has taken over.

36:12.960 --> 36:16.362
PEREZ: Come on.
You're local police.

36:16.400 --> 36:17.811
Work with them.

36:17.840 --> 36:21.640
I'll really make it
worth your while.

36:24.720 --> 36:27.007
OLSON: Well, uh...

36:27.040 --> 36:29.805
that sounds just fine,
Mr. Perez.

36:29.840 --> 36:33.208
PEREZ: This guy
stole $3 million from me.

36:33.240 --> 36:35.925
Now you help me find him...

36:35.960 --> 36:40.170
and I'll give you
a hefty finder's fee.

36:40.200 --> 36:43.966
And then you can just
go on your merry way.

36:44.000 --> 36:47.447
OLSON: Now that sounds
like a good deal.

36:52.960 --> 36:56.328
You gonna keep pointing
that gun at me, partner?

37:02.760 --> 37:05.206
PEREZ: [ Chuckles ] Okay.

37:05.240 --> 37:07.322
You know me.

37:07.360 --> 37:10.170
So you know what happens
if you don't.

37:14.560 --> 37:16.927
OLSON:
That's a hell of a good deal.

37:20.560 --> 37:22.847
PEREZ: Vémanos.

37:24.240 --> 37:26.766
OLSON: It's gonna be a pleasure

37:26.800 --> 37:29.326
doing business with you,
Mr. Perez.

37:45.360 --> 37:46.885
Ahh.

37:46.920 --> 37:48.843
Damn.

37:48.880 --> 37:50.882
Phew.

37:55.680 --> 37:57.011
PEREZ: Something's wrong.

37:57.040 --> 38:00.601
I don't know, but...
he's hiding something.

38:00.640 --> 38:02.881
JOSEPH: He might be playing us.

38:05.560 --> 38:07.767
PEREZ: You know what?

38:07.800 --> 38:10.849
Keep somebody on him.

38:10.880 --> 38:12.803
Let's find out
where it takes us.

38:12.840 --> 38:15.810
JOSEPH: You really plan
on letting him keep the money?

38:15.840 --> 38:19.242
PEREZ: That's loco!
Hell, no. Come on.

38:27.680 --> 38:30.524
[Telephone ringing ]
COLE: Cole.

38:30.560 --> 38:31.971
BLACK:
I'm at the sheriff's house,

38:32.000 --> 38:33.286
and I got a license plate
for you.

38:33.320 --> 38:34.481
Can you run a history?

38:34.520 --> 38:36.090
COLE: Sure.
What are the numbers?

38:36.120 --> 38:41.160
BLACK: Foxtrot, Golf,
Seven, Nine, Six, One, Hotel.

38:41.200 --> 38:45.762
COLE: Okay. Give it a second.

38:45.800 --> 38:47.006
Huh.

38:47.040 --> 38:49.771
People...

38:49.800 --> 38:53.486
this case just got
a lot more interesting.

38:53.520 --> 38:55.124
Mateo Daniel Perez was spotted

38:55.160 --> 38:57.606
at the house of our friendly
neighborhood sheriff.

38:57.640 --> 39:00.928
Now, what's a drug lord
like Mateo

39:00.960 --> 39:03.042
doing hanging out
with the sheriff?

39:03.080 --> 39:05.401
And to top it all off...

39:05.440 --> 39:07.761
I just found out
that our little dead deputy

39:07.800 --> 39:10.963
is the son of the most
successful drug lord ever.

39:11.000 --> 39:12.365
Now, people...

39:12.400 --> 39:15.529
we've had a guy
on the inside of Perez's gang,

39:15.560 --> 39:20.009
but there's been no connection
with the sheriff until now.

39:20.040 --> 39:21.530
What is going on?

39:21.560 --> 39:23.608
People, I need some answers.

39:23.640 --> 39:25.608
I need you to get
your asses out there,

39:25.640 --> 39:27.881
or some heads will roll.

39:27.920 --> 39:30.890
HOWARD: All right. Look.

39:30.920 --> 39:32.888
Let's... Let's try
and stand up back to back, okay?

39:32.920 --> 39:35.446
CHRISTINE: Hell, no.
You're gonna get us killed.

39:35.480 --> 39:37.767
HOWARD:
Just do what I tell you to do!

39:37.800 --> 39:39.928
When I go, "One, two, three,"
back to back,

39:39.960 --> 39:41.644
we're gonna stand up, and
we're get the hell out of here.

39:41.680 --> 39:42.647
CHRISTINE: Hell, no!

39:42.680 --> 39:44.091
HOWARD: Just do it, okay?

39:44.120 --> 39:45.804
One, two, three.

39:45.840 --> 39:47.524
CHRISTINE: Ow. Stop it!

39:47.560 --> 39:49.722
HOWARD: Look, just...

39:49.760 --> 39:51.205
God damn it. Shut up.

39:51.240 --> 39:53.527
- Stand up!
- CHRISTINE: Ow! No!

39:53.560 --> 39:54.971
HOWARD: Stand up with me.
Stand...

39:55.000 --> 39:56.490
CHRISTINE: OW!

39:56.520 --> 39:57.681
HOWARD: Damn it.

39:57.720 --> 39:59.324
CHRISTINE: Will you stop?!

39:59.360 --> 40:02.967
You are such an idiot.
HOWARD: Shit.

40:03.000 --> 40:05.287
You're callin' me an idiot?

40:05.320 --> 40:07.163
When you're dumb as dirt?

40:07.200 --> 40:08.406
Are you kiddin' me?

40:08.440 --> 40:09.601
CHRISTINE: You just shut up.

40:09.640 --> 40:11.085
HOWARD: You shut up! Look.

40:11.120 --> 40:12.531
Do you want him
to come in here and kill us?

40:12.560 --> 40:14.369
CHRISTINE:
We stay here, we wait it out.

40:14.400 --> 40:16.368
And we don't piss him off!

40:16.400 --> 40:19.370
[ Heart beating]

40:24.600 --> 40:26.045
INMATE: Nice work, fish.

40:26.080 --> 40:27.969
We have a job for you
when you get out.

40:28.000 --> 40:30.082
MAN:
What the hell happened to you?

40:30.120 --> 40:33.841
You haven't checked in.
What's going on?

40:33.880 --> 40:35.166
BRIAN: Aah!

40:35.200 --> 40:36.440
- CHRISTINE: Hey!
- HOWARD: What?

40:36.480 --> 40:37.720
What are you doin'?
CHRISTINE: Shh!

40:37.760 --> 40:38.886
HOWARD:
What do you mean, "shh"?

40:38.920 --> 40:41.161
[ Door opens ]

40:41.200 --> 40:42.611
BRIAN: What?

40:43.600 --> 40:45.887
CHRISTINE:
I need to go to the bathroom.

40:45.920 --> 40:47.206
HOWARD: Shut up!

40:47.240 --> 40:48.969
CHRISTINE:
[Whispering ] Shut up.

40:52.640 --> 40:55.291
BRIAN:
Where's your manners, boy?

40:55.320 --> 40:58.164
You don't talk to a woman
like that.

41:00.080 --> 41:01.923
ROOKER:
The suspect used Highway 5

41:01.960 --> 41:03.849
driving into this area.

41:03.880 --> 41:06.804
So we're concentrating
our efforts here.

41:06.840 --> 41:08.649
We have roadblocks
on every highway,

41:08.680 --> 41:10.808
and we're conducting
house-to-house searches.

41:10.840 --> 41:11.921
OFFICER:
Yeah, but how do we know

41:11.960 --> 41:13.644
he didn't ditch his vehicle?

41:13.680 --> 41:15.921
Or maybe took off on foot?

41:19.360 --> 41:21.966
ROOKER: Since we yet
haven't located the van,

41:22.040 --> 41:25.681
we're still assuming
he's in the possession of it.

41:25.720 --> 41:28.200
OFFICER #2: Do we have an I.D.
on the suspect?

41:29.560 --> 41:30.686
ROOKER: Yes.

41:32.480 --> 41:35.962
We've extracted an image
from a street cam.

41:36.000 --> 41:39.288
Waiting for blood DNA analysis.

41:39.320 --> 41:41.926
Haven't yet identified
the suspects.

41:41.960 --> 41:45.248
Please remember, people, this is
the suspect in the murder

41:45.280 --> 41:47.567
of a law-enforcement officer.

41:47.600 --> 41:50.649
I expect you all to be
on your top game for this one.

41:52.120 --> 41:53.690
[ Clears throat]

41:53.720 --> 41:55.722
Any questions?

42:07.280 --> 42:10.648
Let's go catch this guy
before he kills anyone else.

42:15.840 --> 42:17.205
BRIAN: Hurry up.

42:17.240 --> 42:19.288
CHRISTINE: What the hell
are you doing here, Brian?!

42:19.320 --> 42:20.810
BRIAN: Brian?

42:20.840 --> 42:24.242
How do you know my name?
CHRISTINE: Is this a joke?

42:24.280 --> 42:27.204
You're supposed to get me out.
Get me out of this thing.

42:27.240 --> 42:30.005
I waited four hours for you,
and nothin'.

42:30.040 --> 42:31.724
No phone call... nothin'.

42:31.760 --> 42:33.683
And now you show up here,
and you do this shit?

42:33.720 --> 42:36.690
What the hell are you thinkin'?!
And where's Bob?

42:36.720 --> 42:38.643
BRIAN: I have no idea
what you're talkin' about, lady.

42:38.680 --> 42:40.682
I've never seen you before
in my goddamn life.

42:40.720 --> 42:43.564
CHRISTINE: [ Scoffs ]
Are you joking?

42:44.600 --> 42:46.489
What the hell happened?
[ Gasps ]

42:46.520 --> 42:48.488
BRIAN: Back the fuck up.
You understand me?

42:48.520 --> 42:50.727
CHRISTINE:
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

42:50.760 --> 42:52.091
Okay, okay, okay. Okay-

42:52.120 --> 42:54.088
Look at me, Brian.

42:54.120 --> 42:55.565
You know me.

42:55.600 --> 42:57.011
I'm Christine.

42:57.040 --> 42:59.566
I know something
fucked up happened.

42:59.600 --> 43:02.001
But I can help you.

43:02.040 --> 43:04.930
Just put the gun down.

43:04.960 --> 43:08.601
Just put the gun down,
God damn it!

43:11.480 --> 43:13.687
[ Breathes deeply]

43:13.720 --> 43:15.882
Now tell me what happened.

43:15.920 --> 43:17.285
Hmm?

43:20.080 --> 43:22.526
BRIAN: Don't touch me.

43:22.560 --> 43:24.608
CHRISTINE: Just tell me
what happened, honey.

43:29.680 --> 43:31.284
BRIAN: I was shot.

43:31.320 --> 43:33.129
Hit in the head.

43:34.360 --> 43:36.886
I don't know.
It's all just a blur.

43:36.920 --> 43:38.285
CHRISTINE:
Well, what do you remember?

43:38.320 --> 43:40.163
BRIAN: Nothin'. You understand?

43:40.200 --> 43:41.804
I don't remember
a goddamn thing.

43:41.840 --> 43:43.330
CHRISTINE: [ Breathes sharply]

43:43.360 --> 43:48.810
BRIAN: It's all just kind of
faces and noise and shit.

43:49.920 --> 43:52.002
CHRISTINE:
I'm sure it's just temporary.

43:52.040 --> 43:54.122
BRIAN: No! It's not temporary.

43:54.160 --> 43:55.446
I'm in trouble here.

43:55.480 --> 43:57.482
CHRISTINE:
Anything can get fixed.

43:57.520 --> 44:00.967
You'll be fine.
Everything will be fine.

44:01.000 --> 44:03.367
BRIAN: I shot a cop.
I killed him.

44:03.400 --> 44:06.483
I know I shot other people, too.
I just <i>...</i> I just can't remember!

44:06.520 --> 44:07.965
I can't remember
a fucking thing!

44:08.040 --> 44:09.883
CHRISTINE: Now, why would you
go shootin' a cop?

44:09.920 --> 44:11.365
BRIAN:
What was I supposed to do?

44:11.400 --> 44:12.765
Let him take me in?

44:12.800 --> 44:14.962
CHRISTINE: We'll just have
to figure it out...

44:15.000 --> 44:17.321
one thing at a time.

44:17.360 --> 44:20.011
But first...

44:20.040 --> 44:22.327
we got to take care of Howard.

44:22.360 --> 44:23.885
BRIAN: You said I was supposed

44:23.920 --> 44:25.729
to take you away
from all this, right?

44:25.760 --> 44:28.161
- CHRISTINE: That's right.
- BRIAN: Okay.

44:28.200 --> 44:31.044
Well, that explains the money
and what I was doin' there.

44:31.080 --> 44:32.320
CHRISTINE: Money?

44:32.360 --> 44:33.850
What money?

44:35.440 --> 44:36.851
BRIAN:
I didn't tell you about it?

44:36.880 --> 44:40.282
CHRISTINE: How much money
are we talkin' about?

44:44.920 --> 44:46.365
BRIAN: I don't know.

44:46.400 --> 44:48.164
Couple million.
CHRISTINE: [ Gasps ]

44:48.200 --> 44:50.407
BRIAN: Maybe more.

44:52.200 --> 44:56.091
CHRISTINE:
You really are my hero.

44:56.120 --> 44:58.691
Yeah.

44:58.720 --> 45:00.848
My hero.

45:08.680 --> 45:10.682
[ Chuckles ]

45:10.720 --> 45:12.085
BRIAN: Stand up.

45:14.720 --> 45:16.688
Turn around.

45:16.720 --> 45:19.883
CHRISTINE: [Chuckles]
What are you doin', Brian?

45:19.920 --> 45:22.844
[Zipper unzipping ]

45:27.680 --> 45:29.489
[ Chuckles ]

45:32.640 --> 45:36.042
I am gonna take care of you.

