would be just lovely.

48:53.120 --> 48:54.451
CLERK: All right.

48:54.480 --> 48:59.441
ROOKER:
Thank you for your cooperation.

48:59.480 --> 49:01.050
[Sighs]

49:02.840 --> 49:05.684
JESSE: Howdy, Sheriff.

49:08.840 --> 49:10.649
[ Pulsating tone]

49:10.680 --> 49:13.286
[Suspenseful music plays]

49:18.880 --> 49:20.689
[Tone stops ]

49:23.720 --> 49:25.449
OLSON: Jesse!

49:28.800 --> 49:30.006
JESSE: Yes, Sheriff?

49:30.040 --> 49:31.485
OLSON:
What the hell happened in here?

49:31.520 --> 49:32.965
JESSE: Oh.
Those agents came by.

49:33.000 --> 49:34.411
Said they needed some things.

49:34.440 --> 49:35.805
OLSON:
Now, who authorized that?

49:35.840 --> 49:37.410
JESSE: I did, silly.

49:37.440 --> 49:41.206
They had all them badges and
paperwork and, well, you know.

49:41.240 --> 49:43.641
OLSON: Son of a bitch.

49:43.680 --> 49:46.206
JESSE:
Have a good day, Sheriff.

50:26.840 --> 50:28.729
OLSON: Mike.

50:28.760 --> 50:29.886
MIKE: Sheriff.

50:29.920 --> 50:31.445
OLSON: Thanks for meetin' me.

50:31.480 --> 50:33.323
MIKE: Always.

50:33.360 --> 50:35.124
SALLY:
Sheriff, you look like shit!

50:35.160 --> 50:38.164
OLSON: Sally, this is a good day
to mind your own damn business.

50:38.200 --> 50:40.282
SALLY: I heard about
what happened to that kid.

50:40.320 --> 50:41.242
[Liquid pouring]

50:41.280 --> 50:42.611
Sorry about your partner.

50:42.640 --> 50:43.926
OLSON: Thank you, Sally.

50:43.960 --> 50:46.008
